### Core Annotations

Spring Boot provides a rich set of annotations for declaring beans, wiring dependencies, and configuring the application.

#### Stereotype Annotations
- **@Component**: Generic stereotype for any Spring-managed bean.
- **@Service**: Specialization of @Component for service-layer logic.
- **@Repository**: Specialization of @Component for data access; adds persistence exception translation.
- **@Controller**: Specialization for MVC controllers (returns view names).
- **@RestController**: @Controller + @ResponseBody for REST APIs.

#### Configuration Annotations
- **@Configuration**: Declares a class as a source of bean definitions.
- **@Bean**: Declares a single bean produced by a method inside a @Configuration class.

#### Property & External Config
- **@Value**: Injects values from properties files, environment variables, or SpEL expressions.
- **@PropertySource**: Specifies the location of property files to load.

```java
@Configuration
@PropertySource("classpath:app.properties")
public class AppConfig {
    @Value("${app.name}")
    private String appName;

    @Bean
    public MyService myService() {
        return new MyService(appName);
    }
}
```

codeExample:
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;

@Service
public class GreetingService {

    @Value("${greeting.default:Hello}")
    private String defaultGreeting;

    public String greet(String name) {
        return defaultGreeting + ", " + name + "!";
    }
}
